Three usual geoplaninid cutaneous muscle layers present: one circular, two diagonal with decussate fibres, one longitudinal with fibres arranged into bundles (
Table 6
). Dorsally, as well as ventrally, body margins excluded; longitudinal layer partially sunk into parenchyma. Dorsal sunken fibres gathered into well-delimited, compact bundles, 107 µm thick; ventral ones much less numerous, gathered into a layer (45 µm Lowest and highest number of muscle fibres per bundle are given in parenthesis.

